rComments: He was a new professor, and he tried his best. His efforts (and nervousness) made class enjoyable and easy. Although he was at some points monotone, I still believe he is an excellent prof.

Relatively easy prof. Fair, knows and explains the material well, and if you do the homework you'll get an A no problem. BIG downside: MONOTONE!!!! Just soooo boring sometimes; I would fall asleep while sitting in the front row of Marion. Still, got A+ in his course, so can't complain ;)

Great prof, awesome personality and although he has the most monotone voice of all-time, he's a nice guy who knows the material inside-out and teaches it well. His exams were very similar to previous year's exams and were pretty easy. Many of my friends had him for CHM1321 (Organic Chem) and said he totally snaked them; seems like he changed :(

Had him for gen chem.  Very decent prof, slides were very simple and easy to understand with no overlapping useless info.  Midterms and final reflected what we had covered.  Very reasonable.  Heard otherwise from his Organic Chem class however.
Super bon enseigant, les examens sont faciles, la matière est claire et intéressante
HE IS HOT, has a cute french accent and is willing to help constantly. How can you not love this teacher? Defo go for him when taking org chem or else you shall be screwed over
Great Organic Chem prof! Explains everything so well in a course that can be difficult. Very helpful and cares about his students. His notes are great too!

For GenChem I wasn't a fan of Frank's teaching style, however the use of clickers & mastering chem will save your mark. In orgo he is a much more interesting prof. Makes funny little jokes and always comes to class looking like a babe. Love you frank <3 He is very friendly and hosts helpful review sessions before exams.
Great professor, very helpful and he definitely knows his stuff! He is very fair with his exams, as long as you go to class and keep up with the material you wont have any problems.

Loiseau is a great prof and actually gives a damn about teaching. Fully recommend going to his office hours if you don't understand something - he is super helpful. Class mandatory - he hand writes notes & doesn't post them online.

Great prof, hot, very helpful when you go to his office hours. He's willing to help with any problems you have with regards to chem. Midterms were fair and quite simple; very similar to those he posts for practice.
Great Prof, Mid-Terms were easy, but exam was quite difficult. Pay Attention to his examples found in his notes.

One word to describe him: hot. He is also an extremely good prof as well though and very caring. I actually switched into his CHM1321 class because I liked his style so much. Class is mandatory due to clicker use but you can miss up too 5 classes and still get the full marks.

Fantastic prof! He's fresh out of university himself, and he does seem a little nervous and unsure of his teaching style, but he knows the material inside out. I definitely got what I expected from general chemistry!
Since he is so young and new to professing he relates very well to his students. he is VERY fair! his practice midterms were VERY similar to his actual midterms. don't drop him as a prof!!

Pretty decent first year teacher.  Still young, fresh out of uni himself, so he really relates and understands things from the student's point of view.  Midterms and finals are very similar to one another, and cover most of what was covered in class.  Not a whole lot of work is required if you've taken 4U Chem.

Very fair course. You do the work, you get an awesome grade. Period. He's a new prof and you can tell he really cares about doing well, which is great. Not too stuffy or informal. But please, minimize the "reading over a PowerPoint slide" thing. Paying real attention was a huge challenge. At least do the practice problems on the digital overhead!

really good teacher, he always find a way to make his class funny. he's a young teacher and knows about the pros and cons about student life. you have to go to class since he puts blanks to fill up. hope to have him back as a teacher

Pros: midterms were really fair, got us interacted with clickers, young guy who cares about us, very helpful, uses mastering chemistry, encourages us to attend class by leaving blanks on his powerpoints. Cons: speaks too fast or monotone sometimes, reads off slides. Could make class more interesting... Generally not too bad though.

He is a very young prof and he simply read from the slides every class. The lectures were extremely boring and not very useful but luckily he used masteringchemistry which was more clear on several subjects. I wouldn't really recommend him to anyone taking first year chem.
Great guy, great teacher. Uses clickers to keep you involved and bonus marks. Midterms are fair and online assignments are easy marks.

I think it's his first year teaching, looks VERY young and has good sense of humour and personality. Also very intelligent and knows the material inside out, and genuinely cares about students. Kinda boring though, gets monotone, but uses clickers to keep us interacting. Also dont bother buying book, get e-book (you only need for practice problems)
Good
